
Tic Tac Toe Game
Overview
This is a simple Tic Tac Toe game implemented in Kotlin using Android Studio. The game allows two players to take turns marking X or O on a 3x3 grid.
The objective is to align three symbols in a row, column, or diagonal to win the game.

Features
Play Now: Start a new game of Tic Tac Toe.
Play Again: Restart the game after it ends.
Two-player mode: Play with a friend locally on the same device.
Visual indicators for the current player's turn.
Game result display: Announces the winner or a draw at the end of the game.

Installation
1. Clone or download this repository.

2. Copy the following code
git clone <repository-url>

3. Open the project in Android Studio.
4. Sync the Gradle files to install dependencies.
5. Build and run the app on an emulator or a physical Android device.

How to Play
Tap the Play Now button on the home screen to start the game.
Players take turns tapping on the grid to place their X or O.
The first player to align three symbols in a row, column, or diagonal wins.
If all grid spaces are filled and no player wins, the game ends in a draw.
Tap the Play Again button to restart the game.


Technologies Used
Kotlin for programming language.
Android Studio for app development.
XML for designing the user interface.
